The paper proposes a framework for autonomous driving that uses machine learning to predict the impact of actions on the agent's perception of the world. This involves learning predictions relating to the behavior of other agents without explicitly learning their policy or intentions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves learning predictions from visual data, which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of predictions to control a vehicle, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
